\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Simple Weaving
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
For those with the magic of dreams, the line between mundane and magical
 blurs.
 Any character in Dream Form may use their closest matching Weaving Skill
 rather than the usual mundane skill for any roll.
 When she does so to due to someone else's powers or abilities, she may
 do so automatically even if she is not aware of the effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
When she does so as part of an proactive action on her part, this counts
 as a Weaving Action.
 While this isn't blatantly supernatural, it still usually leaves subtle
 tells that something is amiss.
 Perhaps she defies gravity, drifting in the air far longer than she should,
 jumping from building to building.
 Perhaps the motion of her feet don't line up with how fast she moves as
 she runs across the field.
 Any witnesses may roll Perception to notice the incongruence in her actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Dreamweaving!Weaving Actions|)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Evocations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Evocations|(textbf
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Dreamweaving!Evocations|(
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Imagination alone limits the wonders that fill the Sea of Stars.
 In one dream, a couple flies through the skies on wings of light.
 In another, they follow a path carved into the stars to an unknown paradise.
 In dreams, all the colors and images of the subconscious and imagination
 are drawn together into one world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Evocations are the brightest power of the Dreamweavers, allowing them to
 create and do things that can only exist in the world of dreams.
 Through them, they may weave their own wonders into the Sea, reshape the
 darkest nightmare into a happy dream, or even overturn the laws of reality
 for a brief moment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Ideals
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Aspects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Luminous do not use their Weaving Skills directly for their Evocations.
 Instead, they require a deeper understanding of a particular Aspect of
 the dream's 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Characters with the ability to Dreamweave may buy Evocations for 5 Experiences
 each, and Upgrades for Evocations they possess for 2 Experiences each.
 While Evocations are picked from a list, this is an abstraction for the
 convenience of the players.
 In truth, they represent a far more fluid understanding of the principles
 behind the Dream, and ways to manipulate those flows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
While a list of Evocations is given for the convenience of the players,
 in truth, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
While Evocations are purchased from a list of powers, they do not represent
 discrete abilities as the Luminous would think of them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Luminous, in addition, have an affinity for two Weaving Skills.
 They treat those skills as if they were two dots higher when qualifying
 for Evocations and their Upgrades.
 Furthermore, they pay one less Experience when buying Evocations and Upgrades
 associated with those skills.
\end_layout

